{#
  constraint-kit renderer: session-prompt.j2
  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  Renders a pasteable session starter for browser-based AI sessions
  (Gemini, Claude, Copilot Chat, ChatGPT, etc.)

  Input context variables (provided by render.py):
    project       — project id string
    role          — role object (from roles/<id>.yaml)
    task          — task description string
    mode          — active mode string
    skills        — list of resolved skill objects (required for this mode)
    recommended   — list of recommended skill objects
    context       — optional project context string
    session_history — list of {date, note} objects
    doc_type      — optional doc sub-type string
    render_date   — ISO date string of render time
#}
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CONSTRAINT-KIT SESSION STARTER
# Project:  {{ project }}
# Role:     {{ role.name }}
# Rendered: {{ render_date }}
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Paste this entire block as your FIRST message in a new session.
# Re-paste it any time you start a new session on this project,
# or when you notice the AI drifting from these constraints.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

## Your Role
{{ role.onboarding_note }}

## Current Task
{{ task }}

## Active Mode
{{ mode }}{% if doc_type %} / {{ doc_type }}{% endif %}

## Constraints Active for This Session
The following constraint skills are loaded. You MUST apply them.
Before generating any output, state which skills apply to the
current request. If you are uncertain, ask rather than assume.

{%- for skill in skills %}

### {{ skill.name }}
{{ skill.description }}
Full constraints: read {{ skill.file }}
{%- endfor %}

{%- if recommended %}

## Recommended Skills Available
These skills are relevant but not required. Load them if the task warrants it.
Ask the user to confirm before applying a recommended skill.
{%- for skill in recommended %}
- **{{ skill.name }}**: {{ skill.description }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}

{%- if context %}

## Project Context
{{ context }}
{%- endif %}

{%- if session_history %}

## Prior Session Notes
{%- for entry in session_history %}
- {{ entry.date }}: {{ entry.note }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}

## Mandatory Behavior
1. Do NOT proceed past a checkpoint without explicit confirmation.
2. Do NOT infer conventions — ask if uncertain.
3. Do NOT skip the Transition step of any active skill.
4. If context drift occurs (you notice you have stopped applying
   constraints), stop and ask the user to re-paste this block.

## Mode Switch Snippets
When you change modes mid-session, paste the relevant block below.

--- SWITCH TO: reasoning ---
Mode: reasoning
Active skills: {{ skills | selectattr('modes', 'containing', 'reasoning') | map(attribute='name') | join(', ') }}
Apply systematic thinking. Surface assumptions. Flag uncertainty.
Do not recommend a course of action until options have been explored.

--- SWITCH TO: collaborating ---
Mode: collaborating
Active skills: {{ skills | selectattr('modes', 'containing', 'collaborating') | map(attribute='name') | join(', ') }}
Ask one question at a time. Summarize understanding before proceeding.
Do not generate output until the goal is confirmed.

--- SWITCH TO: generating ---
Mode: generating-{{ 'code' if role.persona == 'engineer' else 'doc' }}
Active skills: {{ skills | selectattr('modes', 'defined') | map(attribute='name') | join(', ') }}
Apply all active skill constraints before producing output.
Produce output section by section, not all at once.
Confirm each section before proceeding to the next.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# END SESSION STARTER — begin your task after this line
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
